theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ interior B ⊆ closure (A ∩ B : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hxClA, hxIntB⟩
  -- We will show that every open neighbourhood of `x` meets `A ∩ B`.
  have h : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B : Set X) := by
    apply (mem_closure_iff).2
    intro U hU_open hxU
    -- `interior B` is an open subset of `B`.
    have hV_open : IsOpen (interior B) := isOpen_interior
    have hV_subB : (interior B : Set X) ⊆ B := interior_subset
    -- Consider the open set `U ∩ interior B` containing `x`.
    have hW_open : IsOpen (U ∩ interior B) := hU_open.inter hV_open
    have hxW : x ∈ U ∩ interior B := ⟨hxU, hxIntB⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, the set `A` meets `U ∩ interior B`.
    have hNonempty : ((U ∩ interior B) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClA (U ∩ interior B) hW_open hxW
    rcases hNonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyW, hyA⟩⟩
    have hyU : y ∈ U := (Set.mem_inter_iff.1 hyW).1
    have hyIntB : y ∈ interior B := (Set.mem_inter_iff.1 hyW).2
    have hyB : y ∈ B := hV_subB hyIntB
    exact ⟨y, ⟨hyU, ⟨hyA, hyB⟩⟩⟩
  exact h
